text:
There is no doubt that what he mentioned in his answer regarding the interpretation of the saying of the Exalted: {And whoever does not judge by what Allah has revealed - then it is those who are the disbelievers}, {And whoever does not judge by what Allah has revealed - then it is those who are the wrongdoers}, and: {And whoever does not judge by what Allah has revealed - then it is those who are the defiantly disobedient} is the correct view. He clarified that Kufr is of two types: Major and Minor, just as Zulm (wrongdoing) is two types, and likewise Fisq (disobedience) is two types: Major and Minor.
So whoever deems lawful (Istihalla) ruling by other than what Allah revealed, or adultery, or usury, or other prohibitions agreed upon as forbidden, has disbelieved with Major Kufr, committed Major Zulm, and Major Fisq. And whoever does them without deeming them lawful, his Kufr is Minor Kufr, his Zulm is Minor Zulm, and likewise his Fisq.
This is due to the saying of the Prophet (peace and blessings be upon him) in the hadith of Ibn Masud (may Allah be pleased with him): [Abusing a Muslim is Fusuq and fighting him is Kufr]. He (peace and blessings be upon him) intended by this Minor Fisq and Minor Kufr, and used the expression to deter from this abominable act.
Similarly, his saying (peace and blessings be upon him): [Two things in people are Kufr for them: Defaming lineage and wailing over the dead.] Narrated by Muslim in his Sahih. And his saying (peace and blessings be upon him): [Do not return after me as disbelievers, striking the necks of one another.] Narrated by Al-Bukhari and Muslim from the hadith of Jarir (may Allah be pleased with him). The hadiths with this meaning are numerous.
Therefore, it is obligatory upon every Muslim, especially the people of knowledge, to verify matters and judge them in the light of the Book and the Sunnah and the path of the Salaf of the Ummah, and to beware of the dire path that many people have taken of issuing general judgments without detail.
The people of knowledge must care for calling to Allah (Glorified be He) with detail, clarifying Islam to the people with its proofs from the Book and the Sunnah, encouraging them to be steadfast upon it, advising and counseling in that, along with warning against everything that contradicts the rulings of Islam. By doing so, they would have followed the path of the Prophet (peace and blessings be upon him), the path of his Rightly Guided Caliphs, and his pleased Companions in clarifying the path of truth, guiding to it, and warning against what opposes it, acting upon the saying of Allah (Glorified be He): {And who is better in speech than one who invites to Allah and does righteousness and says, "Indeed, I am of the Muslims."}
And His saying (Mighty and Majestic): {Say, "This is my way; I invite to Allah with insight, I and those who follow me. And exalted is Allah; and I am not of those who associate others with Him."}
And His saying (Glorified be He): {Invite to the way of your Lord with wisdom and good instruction, and argue with them in a way that is best.}
